Content:
Lisp is hardly the only answer.  Smalltalk does this just fine in the Seaside framework, which threw out templates to get rid of this exact mess.  We write our html, server side code, and client side ajax code pretty much entirely in Smalltalk.<p><pre><code>    renderContentOn: html
        50 timesRepeat: 
            [ html div 
                class: #SomeStyle; 
                onClick: (html element hide);
                with: 'Who needs HTML?' ]</code></pre>
